efforts to move beyond such sexist stifling, and the women-led and women-centered spiritual, governance, and activist practices they have engendered in the late twentieth and early twenty-first centuries. Featuring many examples of the sisters’ resourcefulness, resilience, and resistance, this book fills a void in international scholarship on what Canadian Catholic women religious have endured and accomplished. Through interviews and in-depth accounts of the complexities and nuances present in the current and former sisters’ lives, readers will discover their steadfast indomitability as they strategically, and sometimes subversively, innovate their spiritual spaces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCatholic womenzCanada. 0aFeminismxReligious aspectsxCatholic Church. 0aFeminist theology. 0aNunszCanada. 0aWomen in the Catholic ChurchzCanada. 4aReligion. 4aSocial Science: Sociology. 4aSocial Science: Women’s Studies. 7aRELIGION / Sexuality & Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aCatholic sisters.  aRoman Catholic Church.  aWomen religious.  afeminist activism.  afeminist spirituality.  agender discrimination.  agender inequality.  agendered innovation.  ainclusive governance.  amale hierarchy.  anuns.  apatriarchal power.  awomen-centered leadership.  awomen-centered liturgy.  awomen’s resourcefulness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112295540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771122955423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771122955/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  